params.amount: uint256 of the amount the user wants to withdraw;

params._withdrawalFee: uint256 of the fee value, multiply your % value by 10, Example: if you want fee of 0.5% , insert 5;*

params._assetAddress: token address representing your asset to be deposited;
params._controller: address of the controller contract, this contract can trigger the depeg events;
params._name: token name for the ERC1155 mints. Insert the name of your token; Example: Y2K_USDC_1.2$
params._strikePrice: uint256 representing the price to trigger the depeg event;
params._symbol: token symbol for the ERC1155 mints. insert here if risk or hedge + Symbol. Example: HedgeY2K or riskY2K;
params._token: address of the oracle to lookup the price in chainlink oracles;
params._withdrawalFee: Insert withdrawal fee uint256 number in percent * 10 => Example: 0.5% = 5; 1% = 10; 40% = 400;

params.epochBegin: uint256 in UNIX timestamp, representing the begin date of the epoch. Example: Epoch begins in 31/May/2022 at 00h 00min 00sec: 1654038000;
params.epochEnd: uint256 in UNIX timestamp, representing the end date of the epoch and also the ID for the minting functions. Example: Epoch ends in 30th June 2022 at 00h 00min 00sec: 1656630000;

params.assets: uint256 representing how many assets the user wants to deposit, a fee will be taken from this value;
params.id: uint256 in UNIX timestamp, representing the end date of the epoch. Example: Epoch ends in 30th June 2022 at 00h 00min 00sec: 1654038000;
params.receiver: address of the receiver of the shares provided by this function, that represent the ownership of the deposited asset;

returns.shares: how many assets the owner is entitled to, removing the fee from its shares;
